    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-21T06:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-21T06:30:00-05:00" n="537"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.01/170: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Personal Representative of the President in India</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-21T18:00:00+06:30"
                            >April 21, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 22—2:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>208. For the President and Secretary, of State. All India Congress meets
                    Allahabad on April 28. Nehru probably make strong bid to <pb facs="0651" n="639"
                        xml:id="pg_639"/> capture party outright on defense issue, driving Gandhist
                    non-resisters out of picture. Nehru’s hand would he immensely strengthened if
                    Britain, China and United States could issue joint statement Pacific war aims,
                    specifically including freedom, self-determination for India and resolution
                    defend India at all costs. Absolutely necessary to add weight of America, China
                    to British promises to overcome Indian distrust of British which even stronger
                    since Cripps’ failure. If to be done should just precede opening Congress.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
